Six teens rescued after falling through ice on Central Park pond Six teens rescued after falling through ice on Central Park pond  31 PM 
A half-dozen teenagers were rescued after plunging through thin ice over the Central Park Pond on Monday evening, police officials say. 
Responding police and firefighters pulled the teens from the water just before 5:50 p.m.
